LORE mafdet-merchant
FLAGS MAFDET MERCHANT
- First Claw oaths: binding and permanent; breaking one = permanent exclusion
  from Mafdet's trade network; the Claw Mark Registry tracks compliance across
  seasons and voyages
- Swift Court: three-tide judgment; cases must be heard and decided within
  three tides of filing; verdicts are final
- Sand-Sea Carters' Guild: controls Saltglass Reach transit; contracts are
  non-negotiable on route and timing; essential link to pyramid corridor
- Dual attestation costs time and coin but prevents destination-port liability;
  Shoreward House provides bilingual clerks for inland/maritime notation gap
- Tide Ledger Hall recalibrates Saltweight reference weights annually; use
  current Saltweights for bulk pricing; last year's are invalid after calibration
- Quarantine Ledger clearance for pyramid goods: factor clearance time into
  pricing when selling perishable goods from the corridor
~
